WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.760
Now that you know who our sellers are, let's
talk about what we actually offer them.

2
00:00:05.320 --> 00:00:10.140
We will begin by talking about how our
solutions help our sellers, and then we'll move

3
00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:11.940
on to discuss our offer playbook.

4
00:00:12.180 --> 00:00:17.160
Because when you're on the phone, you need to
be able to explain what the BMH Group does

5
00:00:17.160 --> 00:00:18.540
in plain English.

6
00:00:18.940 --> 00:00:23.280
The kind of language where a homeowner who's
never heard of us can understand it in

7
00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.400
about 30 seconds.

8
00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:28.440
We buy houses for cash, as is.

9
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:34.580
No repairs, no agents, no commissions, no
waiting around for months.

10
00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:36.240
That's the whole offer.

11
00:00:36.660 --> 00:00:40.120
But each piece of that matters, so let me
walk through them.

12
00:00:41.280 --> 00:00:45.420
When I say we buy with cash, I mean we don't
go through a bank.

13
00:00:45.900 --> 00:00:49.860
There's no loan approval process, no
appraisal contingency,

14
00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:53.900
no waiting 45 days for underwriting to come
back.

15
00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:57.800
When we say we can close, we mean it.

16
00:00:58.400 --> 00:01:02.920
That gives sellers something they can't get
from most buyers, which is certainty.

17
00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:07.680
They know the deal isn't going to fall apart
two weeks before closing because someone's

18
00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:09.280
financing didn't come through.

19
00:01:10.600 --> 00:01:14.680
As is. The seller doesn't need to fix a
single thing.

20
00:01:15.120 --> 00:01:17.100
Roof leaking? That's fine.

21
00:01:17.100 --> 00:01:20.160
Foundation cracking? We'll handle it.

22
00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:23.620
Hoarding situation with stuff piled to the
ceiling?

23
00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.740
We've walked into plenty of those.

24
00:01:26.260 --> 00:01:30.780
For sellers who can't afford repairs or who
just don't have the energy to manage a

25
00:01:30.780 --> 00:01:34.600
renovation they never wanted in the first
place, this is a big deal.

26
00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:38.100
They can walk away from the property exactly
as it sits.

27
00:01:39.220 --> 00:01:45.280
In a traditional sale, the seller is paying
5 to 6% in real estate commissions.

28
00:01:45.280 --> 00:01:51.720
On a $200,000 house, that's $10,000 to $12
,000 gone before

29
00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:54.980
they see a dime. With us, there are no
commissions.

30
00:01:55.540 --> 00:01:58.520
The number we offer is the number they walk
away with.

31
00:01:59.700 --> 00:02:05.540
A traditional sale takes 60 to 90 days minimum,
and that's if everything goes smoothly.

32
00:02:05.720 --> 00:02:06.820
It often doesn't.

33
00:02:06.820 --> 00:02:09.360
We can close in as little as a week or two.

34
00:02:09.620 --> 00:02:15.060
For someone facing foreclosure, going through
a divorce, or relocating for work on short

35
00:02:15.060 --> 00:02:17.820
notice, that speed changes everything.

36
00:02:19.320 --> 00:02:23.200
When you're explaining our process to a
seller, keep it simple.

37
00:02:23.840 --> 00:02:25.060
There are four steps.

38
00:02:25.540 --> 00:02:29.500
First, we talk. You have a conversation with
the homeowner.

39
00:02:29.860 --> 00:02:34.180
You learn about their situation, their
property, what they need.

40
00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:35.940
That's where the relationship starts.

41
00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:39.800
Second, we look at the property.

42
00:02:40.420 --> 00:02:41.880
Our team evaluates it.

43
00:02:42.260 --> 00:02:45.200
Sometimes that's virtual, sometimes in
person.

44
00:02:45.700 --> 00:02:52.200
We look at the condition, the location, what
comparable houses have sold for, and what

45
00:02:52.200 --> 00:02:54.060
repairs would cost.

46
00:02:55.180 --> 00:02:57.000
Third, we make an offer.

47
00:02:57.820 --> 00:03:01.880
Based on that evaluation, we present a fair
cash offer.

48
00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:04.320
No pressure, no obligation.

49
00:03:05.060 --> 00:03:07.360
If it works for them, we move forward.

50
00:03:07.600 --> 00:03:09.620
If it doesn't, no hard feelings.

51
00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:13.680
We're not going to chase anyone who doesn't
want to do business.

52
00:03:14.700 --> 00:03:20.940
Fourth, we close. Once the seller accepts,
we handle everything from there.

53
00:03:21.340 --> 00:03:24.260
Title work, closing logistics, all of it.

54
00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:30.200
The seller picks their closing date, signs
the paperwork, and gets paid.

55
00:03:31.600 --> 00:03:33.400
Four steps. That's it.

56
00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:38.860
When you can walk a seller through that on
the phone calmly and clearly, you sound like

57
00:03:38.860 --> 00:03:41.700
someone who knows what they're doing,
because you do.

58
00:03:42.700 --> 00:03:45.380
Now, I want to be honest about something.

59
00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:49.020
Sellers don't choose us because we pay the
highest price.

60
00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:51.920
We don't. Our offers are below retail.

61
00:03:52.540 --> 00:03:54.160
That's how this business works.

62
00:03:54.600 --> 00:04:00.140
We buy at a discount because we're taking on
the risk, the repairs, and the costs of

63
00:04:00.140 --> 00:04:02.040
holding and reselling the property.

64
00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:05.400
So why do sellers choose us?

65
00:04:05.980 --> 00:04:07.560
Because of what they get in return.

66
00:04:08.300 --> 00:04:11.320
Speed. They close in days, not months.

67
00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:13.920
Simplicity. No showings.

68
00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:16.560
No open houses. No staging.

69
00:04:17.120 --> 00:04:18.960
No agents going back and forth.

70
00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:25.220
Certainty. Cash means the deal doesn't fall
through because a buyer's loan got denied.

71
00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:28.680
And convenience. We handle everything.

72
00:04:29.260 --> 00:04:31.160
They just sign and walk away.

73
00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:37.740
For a seller who inherited a house 500 miles
away that they haven't been inside in two

74
00:04:37.740 --> 00:04:42.820
years, or someone who's three months behind
on payments with a foreclosure notice on

75
00:04:42.820 --> 00:04:48.880
their kitchen table, or someone staring at a
$50,000 repair bill they'll never be able

76
00:04:48.880 --> 00:04:51.480
to pay, that tradeoff makes sense.

77
00:04:51.480 --> 00:04:53.240
They're not giving up money.

78
00:04:53.640 --> 00:04:56.020
They're buying speed and peace of mind.

79
00:04:56.520 --> 00:05:00.040
You don't need to convince anyone that our
price is the best price.

80
00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:01.460
That's not the job.

81
00:05:01.680 --> 00:05:08.140
The job is helping them see that the total
package, speed, certainty, no hassle, is

82
00:05:08.140 --> 00:05:11.100
the best solution for their specific
situation.

83
00:05:11.660 --> 00:05:14.020
Some people will get that immediately.

84
00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:17.460
Some will need time. Some will never come
around.

85
00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:19.260
All of that is fine.

86
00:05:20.260 --> 00:05:26.760
You should also understand the basics of how
our offers get calculated, even though

87
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:28.260
you're not the one making them.

88
00:05:28.740 --> 00:05:30.060
We look at three numbers.

89
00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:35.660
The after repair value, which is what the
property would sell for on the open market if

90
00:05:35.660 --> 00:05:37.060
it were fully fixed up.

91
00:05:37.380 --> 00:05:41.480
The repair costs, which is what it would
take to get it to that condition.

92
00:05:41.480 --> 00:05:47.920
And our offer, which is the after repair
value minus the repairs minus our

93
00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:50.220
margin for profit and carrying costs.

94
00:05:50.760 --> 00:05:52.200
That's how we get to a number.

95
00:05:53.080 --> 00:05:58.880
Here's an example. A house has an after
repair value of $200,000.

96
00:05:59.380 --> 00:06:01.940
It needs $50,000 in work.

97
00:06:02.340 --> 00:06:08.320
After accounting for our costs, we might
offer somewhere around $100,000 to

98
00:06:08.320 --> 00:06:13.220
$110,000. Is that less than $200,000?

99
00:06:13.420 --> 00:06:14.140
Obviously.

100
00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:17.620
But the seller was never going to get $200
,000.

101
00:06:18.120 --> 00:06:24.480
Not without putting in $50,000 in repairs,
paying $12,000 in commissions, and waiting

102
00:06:24.480 --> 00:06:25.900
four months for a buyer.

103
00:06:26.260 --> 00:06:31.200
When you actually do the math, our offer
isn't as far off as it sounds on the surface.

104
00:06:32.180 --> 00:06:35.980
Last thing. When a seller asks you, how does
this work?

105
00:06:36.420 --> 00:06:38.980
On the phone, here's how you answer it.

106
00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:44.660
In your own words, something like, we buy
houses directly from homeowners for cash.

107
00:06:45.040 --> 00:06:46.680
You don't need to make any repairs.

108
00:06:47.080 --> 00:06:48.980
You don't pay any commissions or fees.

109
00:06:48.980 --> 00:06:52.180
And we can close on whatever timeline works
for you.

110
00:06:52.180 --> 00:06:58.100
We take a look at the property, put together
a fair offer, and if it works for you, we

111
00:06:58.100 --> 00:06:59.820
handle everything from there.

112
00:07:00.500 --> 00:07:03.360
Practice saying that until it flows
naturally.

113
00:07:03.860 --> 00:07:08.020
Remember, it shouldn't sound memorized or
robotic.

114
00:07:09.060 --> 00:07:14.260
The best way to truly internalize a script
is to write it out by hand.

115
00:07:14.760 --> 00:07:17.500
That's right. Grab a pen and paper.

116
00:07:18.080 --> 00:07:22.620
Writing engages your brain in a different
way and helps reinforce the words.

117
00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:26.760
Plus, it makes the delivery feel more
authentic and personal.

118
00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:32.980
So, take a moment, jot it down, and watch
how much easier it becomes to express those

119
00:07:32.980 --> 00:07:34.900
thoughts with confidence and ease.

120
00:07:35.420 --> 00:07:38.020
Remember this when you are struggling
handling an objection.

121
00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:43.400
Alright, quick deep dive next to lock the
full offer playbook in.
